g.text: UML Diagram: Class Signifier in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.

a.title: ― Sign: Something that suggests the presence or existence of a fact, condition, or quality.
a.xlink:title: ― Sign: Something that suggests the presence or existence of a fact, condition, or quality.

a.title: ― Signified: Concept or object denoted by the signifier associated to a sign.
a.xlink:title: ― Signified: Concept or object denoted by the signifier associated to a sign.

a.title: ― Signifier: Concept whose extension includes perceivable objects.
a.xlink:title: ― Signifier: Concept whose extension includes perceivable objects.

a.title: ― WhiteSpaceRule: WhiteSpace constrains the value space of types derived from string.
a.xlink:title: ― WhiteSpaceRule: WhiteSpace constrains the value space of types derived from string.

a.title: ― InstanceValue: Single data instance corresponding to a concept (with a notion of equality defined) being observed, captured, or derived.
a.xlink:title: ― InstanceValue: Single data instance corresponding to a concept (with a notion of equality defined) being observed, captured, or derived.

a.title: ― Notation: Representation of a category in the context of a code or a classification item, as opposed of the corresponding instance value which would appear when used in a dataset.
a.xlink:title: ― Notation: Representation of a category in the context of a code or a classification item, as opposed of the corresponding instance value which would appear when used in a dataset.
